---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "SKS Stove Repair | Southern California | Signature Kitchen Suite Combi-Induction";
const description = "Signature Kitchen Suite stove repair across Southern California — pro-style 30/36/48, sous-vide drawer, combi-induction gas + induction hybrid. LG luxury since 2016. $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/signature-kitchen-suite-stove-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is SKS (Signature Kitchen Suite) really an LG brand?",
    a: "Yes — <b>Signature Kitchen Suite (SKS)</b> is LG Electronics' luxury residential appliance line, launched in 2016 specifically to give LG a pro-style luxury play distinct from mainstream LG-branded appliances. LG Electronics is the corporate parent; SKS operates as a dedicated brand with separate marketing, dealer network, and product engineering for luxury-tier features. Not to be confused with mass-market LG-branded stoves — different platform, different parts channel at authorized service, different positioning. For service context: SKS parts flow through LG's US parts distribution with SKS-specific component catalogs; SKS-specific innovations (sous-vide drawer, combi-induction cooktop) are engineered on SKS platform rather than pulled from LG mainstream. If you own mass-market LG pro-style, see <a href='/brands/lg-stove-repair/'>LG stove repair</a> for the mainstream line; this page covers SKS luxury pro-style only."
  },
  {
    q: "What makes combi-induction on SKS different?",
    a: "SKS's combi-induction pro-range is the stove brand's distinctive feature: a single cooktop combines traditional gas burners with induction zones in the same cooking surface (rather than separate gas-only or induction-only stoves). Typical configurations on SKS pro-range: 3-4 gas burners + 2-3 induction zones on 36\", with larger-format 48\" adding wok + griddle options. The practical angle: induction gives instant on-off precision for delicate work (sauce reductions, chocolate tempering); gas gives open-flame cooking for wok-style high-heat and gas-specific cooking methods. Service on combi-induction is split between gas-side diagnostics (conventional pro-range: orifice, spark, thermocouple) and induction-side diagnostics (coil, induction control board, thermal sensor). SKS-specific engineering means the combi-induction control logic is distinct from mass-market induction cooktops."
  },
  {
    q: "SKS sous-vide drawer not maintaining temperature — what's failing?",
    a: "SKS built a sous-vide drawer into the pro-range as a dedicated water-bath cooking zone (claimed first-in-category at 2016 launch). When sous-vide temperature stability fails: (1) water-bath heating element — dedicated element for the drawer; swap $380–$560; (2) drawer temperature sensor — precision control depends on accurate sensor; sensor $260–$400 (SKS sous-vide sensors are higher-precision than standard oven sensors); (3) control board with sous-vide-specific logic — board swap $480–$660; (4) water-level sensor — sous-vide can't run dry; sensor replacement $220–$320; (5) drawer seal — sous-vide drawer must hold water + stable temperature, seal degradation affects thermal control; seal $180–$280. SKS sous-vide service requires SKS-specific parts through LG authorized channel — 7-14 day lead typical on sous-vide-specific components (less common demand drives longer stock cycling than main-oven components)."
  },
  {
    q: "SKS gas burner not lighting — diagnostic order?",
    a: "Standard pro-range gas diagnostic: (1) orifice verification — propane / natural gas mismatch on rental / sold-home installs; orifice swap $180–$280 per burner (SKS orifices are LG-specific, not interchangeable with mass-market LG parts); (2) spark-module ignition — aging at 7-10 year mark on current-generation SKS; swap $280–$400; (3) ignitor tip clean / replace $200–$300; (4) thermocouple flame-failure $220–$320; (5) burner cap seating + port clean $160–$240 per burner; (6) gas valve partial restriction $300–$440; (7) regulator pressure stability $220–$320. Our techs carry SKS-specific igniters + thermocouples in LA dispatch; LG US parts channel typical 5-10 day lead on common SKS service components through SKS-authorized service network."
  },
  {
    q: "SKS induction zone not heating — is it a coil or control problem?",
    a: "SKS induction diagnostic: (1) cookware compatibility — induction requires ferromagnetic cookware; confirm pan is magnetic; (2) induction coil — coil swap $340–$500 per zone (SKS induction coils are LG-sourced but SKS-specific firmware); (3) combi-induction control board — dedicated board handles induction zones + communicates with gas-burner control logic; board swap $500–$680; (4) power supply continuity — 240V supply drop affects induction zones; supply diagnostic $180–$280; (5) under-hob thermal sensor — surface-temp protection cutout; sensor $220–$320. Combi-induction diagnostic requires SKS-specific service approach because induction + gas share control-logic integration — we diagnose whether fault is in induction-side (coil, induction board), gas-side (separate), or cross-system (combi control logic) before quoting repair."
  },
  {
    q: "How does SKS service cost compare to Wolf or Thermador?",
    a: "SKS sits at pro-luxury tier pricing comparable to Wolf / Thermador on most service items. Diagnostic standard residential $89 waived with repair. Individual parts: orifice $180–$280, spark $280–$400, thermocouple $220–$320, oven igniter $260–$380, convection fan $340–$500, control board $460–$680, element $320–$460 — all within 10-15% of Wolf / Thermador equivalents. Where SKS economics diverge: (1) sous-vide drawer + combi-induction specialty parts run 7-14 day lead (less common stock) vs 1-5 days on pure gas-pro-range components; (2) SKS-specific firmware updates occasionally part of service when control-logic issues surface; (3) LG parts channel supports SKS legacy units (2016+) well, but 10-year-plus platform component-level parts have not yet hit end-of-life (first SKS cohort still at 9-year mark). Service-life expectation 15-20+ years on pro-style SKS with periodic parts servicing — typical luxury-category standard."
  },
  {
    q: "SKS vs LG mass-market pro-style — same parts?",
    a: "No — SKS parts and LG mass-market parts are separate catalogs despite shared LG corporate parent. SKS components are engineered for luxury-tier service life and SKS-specific innovations (sous-vide drawer, combi-induction control logic, higher-grade igniter + sensor specs); LG mass-market pro-style components are sourced from LG's mainstream supply chain. At diagnostic we verify model number + serial to route parts through correct LG channel — SKS-authorized service has SKS-specific catalog access, mainstream LG service cannot typically source SKS-specific parts. If you have mass-market LG pro-style, different service economics + different parts-channel expectations apply — see <a href='/brands/lg-stove-repair/'>LG stove repair</a>. Our service handles both but via separate parts-sourcing workflows."
  },
  {
    q: "What does SKS stove repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Typical SKS bands: orifice swap (per burner) $180–$280; burner cap replacement $140–$220; spark-module ignition $280–$400; ignitor tip clean / replace $200–$300; thermocouple flame-failure $220–$320; air-mixture adjustment $180–$260; gas-line regulator $220–$320; gas valve swap $300–$440; oven igniter $260–$380; bake element $320–$460; convection element $320–$460; convection fan motor $340–$500; temperature sensor $220–$320; thermal fuse $240–$340; control board (main oven) $460–$660; combi-induction control board $500–$680; induction coil $340–$500 per zone; induction thermal sensor $220–$320; sous-vide drawer heating element $380–$560; sous-vide precision sensor $260–$400; sous-vide control board $480–$660; water-level sensor $220–$320; oven door rope seal $180–$280. Specialty sous-vide + combi-induction parts carry 7-14 day lead; core pro-range gas parts 5-10 day lead."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Signature Kitchen Suite Stove Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Signature Kitchen Suite Stove Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Signature Kitchen Suite (SKS) stove repair across Southern California — LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. pro-style 30/36/48 freestanding, combi-induction hybrid gas + induction cooktop, sous-vide drawer, steam + convection oven configurations. LG Electronics luxury brand since 2016. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Signature Kitchen Suite", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/signature-kitchen-suite/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "SKS Stove Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>SKS stove service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Signature Kitchen Suite › Stove Repair</div>
    <h1>Signature Kitchen Suite (SKS) Stove Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Signature Kitchen Suite is LG Electronics' luxury residential appliance brand, launched in 2016 as LG's dedicated pro-style luxury play — distinct from mainstream LG-branded appliances with separate engineering, dealer network, and parts catalogs. SKS's distinctive features on pro-range stoves are the combi-induction cooktop (mixing gas burners + induction zones on the same surface) and the built-in sous-vide drawer for dedicated water-bath precision cooking. Pro-style 30"/36"/48" freestanding configurations with steam + convection oven variants cover the residential lineup. Our LA SKS service works through LG authorized parts channel with SKS-specific catalogs — separate from mass-market LG pro-style service. Concentrated installs in Bel Air + Beverly Hills luxury remodels, Pacific Palisades architectural custom, Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal luxury, Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-district kitchens choosing combi-induction for cooking-method flexibility. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>LG luxury brand since 2016</b> — separate from mainstream LG</li>
      <li><b>Combi-induction cooktop</b> — gas + induction hybrid on same surface</li>
      <li><b>Sous-vide drawer</b> — dedicated water-bath precision cooking zone</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>SKS in LA — newer luxury entrant with distinct cooking-mode innovations</h2>
    <p>SKS is a newer entrant in the LA luxury-stove installed base — most SKS units in LA are 2018-2024 production from the brand's second and third design-generation cycles. The combi-induction cooktop is the specific feature driving SKS selection in LA custom kitchens: households that want induction precision for specific cooking tasks but don't want to give up gas-flame capability pick SKS over a pure-gas Wolf / Viking / BlueStar or a pure-induction Gaggenau. Sous-vide drawer is the secondary driver — cooking-enthusiast households that use sous-vide as a daily cooking method (not just occasional) select SKS specifically for the built-in precision.</p>
    <p>LA SKS service geography tracks design-district + cooking-enthusiast installs. Bel Air + Beverly Hills custom kitchens with combi-induction flexibility; Pacific Palisades + Brentwood architectural remodels; Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-district kitchens; Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal luxury. Service approach on SKS reflects the brand's dual-technology complexity: we diagnose gas-side and induction-side faults separately before attributing fault to combi-control logic. Sous-vide drawer service requires SKS-specific parts on 7-14 day lead typically — less common stock cycling than main-oven components. Our techs diagnose firmware-vs-hardware on SKS control faults since LG firmware updates occasionally resolve combi-induction communication faults without hardware replacement.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>SKS stove failures our techs see most often</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Combi-induction zone not heating</h3><p>Coil swap $340–$500 per zone; combi-induction control board $500–$680; thermal sensor $220–$320. Firmware update sometimes resolves communication faults.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Sous-vide drawer temperature instability</h3><p>Heating element $380–$560; precision sensor $260–$400; sous-vide control board $480–$660; water-level sensor $220–$320.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Gas burner no-light — orifice / spark / thermocouple</h3><p>Standard pro-range diagnostic. Orifice $180–$280 per burner; spark $280–$400; thermocouple $220–$320.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven temperature drift</h3><p>Sensor $220–$320; control board $460–$660; element $320–$460 on dual-fuel / electric-oven variants.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Convection fan motor</h3><p>Motor swap $340–$500. Convection element $320–$460.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Combi-control communication fault</h3><p>Gas-side + induction-side integration logic. Firmware update first, hardware diagnostic second. Board swap only when firmware-isolated.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>SKS stove product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pro-style 30"</h3><p>Compact pro-range. All-gas + combi-induction + sous-vide drawer configurations.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pro-style 36" (most common)</h3><p>Luxury-kitchen standard size. 4 gas + 2 induction combi common. Sous-vide drawer optional.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pro-style 48"</h3><p>Large-format custom kitchens. 4 gas + 3 induction + griddle options. Double-oven + steam + convection variants.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Combi-induction cooktop (signature)</h3><p>Gas burners + induction zones on same cooking surface. SKS distinctive engineering.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Sous-vide drawer (signature)</h3><p>Dedicated water-bath precision cooking. Built into pro-range format. SKS-specific feature.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Steam + convection oven variants</h3><p>Steam oven module adds precision steam cooking. Convection bake + roast + proof cycles.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>SKS vs LG mass-market vs Wolf / Thermador</h2>
    <p>SKS occupies a distinct position: LG-parent luxury with pro-range innovations (combi-induction, sous-vide drawer) that LG mass-market doesn't offer.</p>
    <p><b>SKS (this page)</b> — LG luxury 2016+, combi-induction + sous-vide drawer, separate parts catalog from mass-market LG. Newer entrant in luxury category.</p>
    <p><b>LG mass-market pro-style</b> — LG mainstream brand, different engineering + different parts channel, more accessible pricing. See <a href="/brands/lg-stove-repair/">LG stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Wolf / Thermador / Viking</b> — established residential luxury (decades-longer installed base), pure-gas or dual-fuel configurations, no combi-induction or sous-vide drawer features. See <a href="/brands/wolf-stove-repair/">Wolf stove repair</a>, <a href="/brands/thermador-stove-repair/">Thermador stove repair</a>, <a href="/brands/viking-stove-repair/">Viking stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p>Choice drivers: SKS for combi-induction cooking-method flexibility + sous-vide integration; established luxury for heritage + installed-base service depth.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What SKS stove repair typically costs</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
